`#pragma once` is a non-standard but widely supported preprocessor directive that instructs the compiler to include the file only once during the compilation process, preventing multiple inclusions. It functions similarly to traditional include guards but often requires less code and reduces the possibility of naming conflicts. It is generally considered safe to use in most modern compilers.

